################
# Browserslist #
################
# [OVERVIEW] Supported browsers’ configuration for Autoprefixer, stylelint and some another tools:
# http://browserl.ist/
#
# [INFO] List of supported browsers:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist#browsers
#
# [INFO] Tools that use browserslist:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist-example
#
# [INFO] Operators “and”, “not”, “or” in configuration file:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist#query-composition
#
# [INFO] Debug — run “npx browserslist” to see supported browsers:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist#debug
#
# [INFO] Links to UC, QQ and Baidu browsers:
# https://github.com/Fyrd/caniuse/issues/4463#issuecomment-420143525
#
# [NOTE] This configuration file doesn’t support multiline comments


# [REQUIRED] Included versions, not solely excluded.
#
# [NOTE] Last 1 version, not last 2,
# because last but one version for some mobile browsers in Can I Use is too obsolete.
# Examples for Android Browser, Opera Mobile and Blackberry Browser:
# version 67 after 4.4.4, version 10 after 7, version 46 after 12.1:
# https://i.imgur.com/hokFRl6.png
last 1 version


# [INFO] As of September 2022, Can I Use use an outdated 2020-year version of QQ Browser:
# https://i.imgur.com/AOcKmg5.png
not and_qq > 0


# [INFO] As of September 2022, Can I Use use an outdated 2016-year version of UC Browser:
# https://i.imgur.com/VLCR0FM.png
not and_uc > 0


# [INFO] As of September 2022, Can I Use use an outdated 2017-year version of Baidu Browser:
# https://i.imgur.com/0FtxTzY.png
not baidu > 0


# [NOTE] 1. BlackBerry discontinued;
# 2. Usage stats are 0.02% for February 2019:
# https://caniuse.com/usage-table
# http://bit.ly/2BGZD7k
not bb > 0


# [INFO] Doesn't support any browser version:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist/issues/137
#
# [INFO] I don’t support any Internet Explorer version. Reasons:
# https://www.lifewire.com/why-do-people-hate-internet-explorer-3485786
# https://www.quora.com/Is-Internet-Explorer-really-as-bad-as-everyone-tries-to-make-out
#
# [NOTE] “not ie, ie_mob > 0”, “not ie and ie_mob > 0” or “not ie > 0 and ie_mob > 0” doesn't work
# We need duplicates “not {browser} > 0”
not ie > 0
not ie_mob > 0


# [INFO] As of September 2022, Can I Use use an outdated 2018-year version of KaiOS:
# https://i.imgur.com/Hw7fH4F.png
not kaios > 0


# [INFO] Opera Mini “is a joke, circumventing rather than supporting the intentions of web developers”:
# https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-best-browser-for-developers/answer/Mack-Moore-1
# https://caniuse.com/#compare=ios_saf+12.2,op_mini+all,android+67,op_mob+46,and_chr+71,and_ff+64,and_qq+1.2
#
# [NOTE] “op_mini all” — ignore all versions of Opera Mini:
# https://github.com/browserslist/browserslist/issues/137#issuecomment-455494613
not op_mini all > 0
